scene.message:
Nanjo: Mirrors have long been{nl}
said to hold spiritual power.{nl}
You think that one has such{nl}
power too?{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: You've suddenly turned{nl}
studious. Think it might{nl}
snow or something?{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: It's musty in here,{nl}
but the atmosphere's not bad.{nl}
Maybe this mirror's{nl}
protecting it.{waitkey}{ret}

Man: I came to see this{nl}
museum's centerpiece, the{nl}
"Evil-Warding Mirror." Truly,{nl}
how divine it is.{waitkey}{ret}

Girl: They say the{nl}
"Evil-Warding Mirror" was the{nl}
only thing found in some{nl}
ruins half a year ago.{waitkey}{clearbox}There's nothing else there,{nl}
so going in is boring — that's{nl}
what my teacher said.{waitkey}{ret}
